Cheese does not come on the "Bean n Cheese" burritos ... Prepare to pay 1$ more for it .
Delish ;)' !!
Watching all the food come out , everything looks amazing ! Celebrating national Hot dog day !
Chicken is really flavorful !
Fresh food .. Upgrade to white meat chkn ... Mmm mmm good
Fresh :) for fast food !
If it's your 1st time talk to girls about your goal so you purchase the right juice ;)
Bacon board !! And wells jack n coke !
Try the moonshine sampler ! Yum !
Best Thai food in Az
Best Thai food in Phoenix!
Pleased as usual
Best Vietnamese food that I've ever had in the valley.
The oatmeal is amazing!
Nice outdoor patio
Eat before you come. The food is way over priced.
Very clean and highly pleased with their service. Nice ambiance.
Great pub with friendly people!
Felt like a cattle call. Bad customer service and I was seated at I dirty table. I left without ordering.
Good gas station with a convenient store.
Good selection and the staff is super helpful.
The sushi was on point! Lot's of options to choose from and all at a great price!
I'm always pleased when I come to this restaurant. The food is wonderful!
Always pleased with the wash!
Nice place if you're ok dining with dogs!
Good food and for the price.
Highly impressed with the chicken shawarma!
The spring rolls were hard, chewy and didn't taste fresh. The worst I've ever had.
Always good.  Highly recommend this place for some Thai food
The food is delicious but the service is slow, even on a weekday
Authentic
The food was delicious and a really cool vibe in old town Litchfield park
Let's just say I had the runs all day

Lunch hour is hopping but staff remains calm and very friendly. The beef panang lunch portion is generous beyond my expectation. Also the level of spice is just perfect without being overpowering hot. You get choice of tom yum gain or egg roll. Both were relish.

Alisha is such a doll and so helpful. Was surprised at the limited type of brushes and paint trays avail. Seems geared more to contractors than homeowners or doityourselfers. In any event, great colors to choose from.

You seriously can't beat their lunch specials from sushi to noodle bowls. I love the Beef Nanban Udon. Pure goodness. The portions are generous and priced beyond a bargain. Love the desserts as this is my weakness. And of course, service is sweet and friendly. If you have a sweeter tooth, go next door to Snoh for shaved ice or boba!

Such a wonderful spot for conferences or meetings. Easy parking without the fuss especially if it's an early meeting. Great staff. Delish breakfast and lovely setup! Not to mention, the golfing here is pretty awesome too.

This is a fast paced and pretty intense class for prepping on your state exam. Be prepared to go from 0 to 60 on insurance matters. Great instructor who is to the point and engaging. Take notes. Have highlighter and strong coffee!!!
Plant seeds of happiness and grab these lovelies for only $7 and spread happiness around your office space

I can't gush enough about this place. Buy their herbs. They flourish tenfolds even in the containers. Their return\/exchange policy on florals is unmatched. I bought peonies that wilted within 24 hours but they exchanged them with no hassle or trouble. You have my heart and loyalty!

I adore this little spot. The staff is always so pleasant. They have wonderful coffee but I cannot resist the tea here. Try the hibiscus flower or the caramel almond though the mandarin orange is a melody of calm and peacefulness soothing to the soul.

Seriously $2.50 for all items. You get the impressive service of a high end cleaner without breaking your bank. Staff is always happy and friendly. And if you refer someone they give you credit towards future bill. Amaze balls!!!

Apparently you can buy lottery tickets while waiting on your baggage. Maybe your odds are better from all the travelers. Love the Starbucks located on that level. Who would have thought you would have fun kicking it while waiting for your ride?!!
If you need to be transported out of the desert, have the coconut mojito. They have some of the best calamari with that awesome sauce. Portions are generous so you can pig out too!

Great HH because lasts til 7p given they open at 5p. HH menu is perfect if you're not looking for a heavy meal. The calamari is the right level of spice with the sweetness to tone it down. I loved the Colby Red so much I should have ordered a bottle since I drank that much. The HH burger is ridiculously huge and the filet mignon flatbread is scrumptious. Sit at the bar and have Brandon serve you.

Any girl knows finding a good salon is like finding a good guy. It's a rarity, you better hang on to it. Prices are affordable and service is stellar! They can get slammed so call ahead. Offers full service from waxes to lashes to your usual mani\/pedi. Impressed by the massaging chairs and cleanliness of spa. Best part, they put on football during weekends or talk shows weekday if you need to zone out. You'll always leave polished hands for arm wrestling or with perfect toes to play footsie.

Cheap and good. They had me with online ordering. One of my go to dives for Chicago hot dogs. Triple up with extra peppers because they are that good!!! And if you can't decide, grab the humongous calzone and philly steak sandwich to go. There was a reason I stayed away, it's addictive and I will most likely be back 3x this week!!!!

This place is just classy and unpretentious. I prefer the bar seating but for dinner meetings, you can't go wrong. Everything is fantastic. Service is phenomenal. Bit older crowd but I like sophistication. Wedge salad is perfect starter and dine on steak or the sea bass. While I opted out this time, the sundae is serious orgasmic delight.

This is a great park tucked away from the busyness of Old Town. Clean and well lit for your evening runs. There's workout stations if you're ambitiously trying to get fit. Best part, you might get lucky and catch an awesome sunrise\/sunset view that makes those miles worthwhile.

This location is stellar. Clean and staff is efficient and super customer service-oriented.  They seriously make life's little mishaps a walk in the park. Kudos to management for having people who delight their customers!!!!
Seriously love this location. Always honest and friendly. And free air check makes me even more loyal customer.

The only reason I checked in is because Alex is the most awesome wine master there! This location is beautiful. Houses my fave Starbucks and has an in-store bar. Why shop? Just hang out and have some drinks! Oh grab the Uneducated Guess Cab and Bailey's Vanilla Cinnamon for your stash!
Serious treasure trove, including the shoppers. I would buy them. Always clean and staff is amazing. I get suckered by the wine sale and end up walking out like an alcoholic on red wines.
My fave HH location. Great people watching. Have the Vegas roll, the garlic citrus yellowtail and the rainbow roll. Perfect flavors to compliment the potstickers and your Sapporo beer!

Best happy hour menu that includes dinner entrees! Mojitos are only $3. Say no more. I am weak. Order the ceviche, albondigas, maduros to start off your experience. Trust me on the flavor medley. Then have the bistec steak, pollo cubano or chicharrones for dinner. OMG. I don't do beans but their rice and beans I will devour.
They have Gold Peak Tea!!!! So delish
Unplug with their happy hour specials and beautiful views of the course!
The grilled sirloin is great lunch portion of protein and healthiness. Tomatoes were bit overpowered by garlic but still yummy!
So it seems if you come midweek particularly Wednesday you get a free oil change with Yelp checkin. This happy camper will save for next use. Thanks for the love Infiniti!

This place is a hidden gem. The quality of work is stellar. I've been coming here since I first sashayed in heels. My travel luggage that has more boxing matches from the conveyor belt of the airport gets first class treatment. I adore the owners that run it. No BS. Just good service and quality workmanship. I almost don't want to share this secret. Come on, I break my code and drive miles just to have my items pampered by them.

Madhouse is understatement. Could explain why every adult seems to have a drink in hand. The energy will either drain you or energize you to find your inner kid joining them in the jungle gym. Usual games to kill time until the kids pass out.

Authentic Thai food. Not for your American palate. I suggest Malee's for those unadventurous. I love the sticky rice and beef jerky with the papaya salad with crab. Just don't plan on kissing a boy. Holy hot dragon breath. Maybe slurp the sukiyaki soup to ease the fire.

This place is never short of energy. Come with anticipation of good things come to those who wait. In meantime, grab a latte from coffee bar while waiting for table. Weekends I would recommend coming early and having the pitcher of mimosas. My fave is the steak and eggs or mignon bene. I also like the Lean & Mean omelette. Generous portions so I am the last person to vote for smaller portions. Is that really an issue for some? Pass it over to me then.
The music is always good. The crowd is always fun. And the wine selection never disappoints. What more do you need?

Purchased a gift online and was able to do in-store pickup on the same day. During the time they received and processed my order, I was kicking weights around at the gym. Seriously Nordy can you just take over life? While you are at it, can I place an order for my future boyfriend?! This is my idea of mail order. There's reason I am faithful to Nordstrom.

I adore this unassuming spot. Parking is limited and tiny so wait can be long on weekends. I never have waffles unless it is here and it's the coconut waffle. OMG. I feel transported to a paradise vacay. And my other favorite is the Continental Crepes. I would like to smother myself with the sauce. Enough said. My smile is a picture of their perfection.

Super ahmazing vibe. I'm attracted to happy people. Get here early otherwise bust out crazy ninja moves to score seat or flash a dazzling smile. Drinks are strong so munch on the incredible fish tacos, insanely good ahi with guacamole. Sip slowly on the Martinis then move to the Huckleberry Margarita and tequila flight.

Take out is quick. Egg rolls are decent and good. Would prefer more lettuce to wrap in. Dipping sauce is purely fish sauce so if you're not Asian, ask for sweet and sour sauce. Pho broth is ok, not going to have the heavens open up in your mouth. It's my second choice since Scottsdale lacks ethnic food.

My fave is coconut iced coffee or their regular with two shots hazelnut with soy milk. Always grab the cruellers bc they won't last. Friendly staff and service is good despite busy hours. Patio is loud since you back up against Hayden. Highly suggest walking over to Pig and Pickle after. But that's just me.
Definitely have the tequila shrimp, a bowl of the chicken tortilla and the green chile mac and cheese. It's enough carbs to fill your happy belly content.

Use your Yelp checkin for the chips and salsa. OMG. Such uhmazing salsa both the green and red. I have to admit that the appetizer filet mignon taco plate and bowl of tortilla soup was so filling I had to ask for a to go box. Wow. Happy belly!

This location is smallest I've been but my local dive. It's dark inside so perfect for recovery on hangovers. I prefer patio because well I'm a desert native who likes the heat. Best wings are the honey hot naked, get an extra side of celery!!!! Otherwise grab the burger with green chili. Will say the turkey burger is not bad alternative. I like the eclectic crowd, no one bites and everyone loves football.

If you need a reward for being good or just want to consume 3000 calories, have the chocolate chip cookie with scoops of vanilla ice cream. Soft gooey yet crispy and buttery. Oooeemgee! There's option of white chocolate macadamia or brownie but this seriously is explosions of happiness.

I love this neighborhood gem especially for late nights at the office bc I can grab HH food and prices anytime from Sunday through Wednesday all night. Order the vodka penne with a side of meatballs (3 in my case. Amaze balls!) with the chicken caesar salad and a glass of Pinot Noir and you feel like an accomplished adult. Cheers!

Who says money can't buy happiness never shopped at Trader Joe's. For under $20, you can have a bottle the Caretaker Pinot Noir, chocolate bonbons and fresh lovelies. Date nights are an every day thing here!

Really laid back place with a vibe for the natives of St. Louis. Staff is always friendly especially at the bar. Love that Happy Hour is til 7p and full menu til midnight. Could not resist the bison sliders and go to  is the filet cooked perfectly. It's dark so adjust your eyes. Hint to the men, it's the spot if you want to go stealth or check out the eye candy before they start their shift at Babe's.

This is a great spot where for under $10 you can grab a bucket of balls and a drink and take your frustrations out. Work on your swing til dark if you have to. It's well lit and open til 9pm. By then, you'll recover from a crappy day :)

I like that they have cheap beer every day, all day. Who complains about $1.50 Bud Lights and $1.99 Heinekens!!! Have to say, the house low mein  was super salty though generous in portion. Loved the wonton soup but comes in cup size on menu. Ask for larger and you get charged double. Good thing they have flyer coupons you can apply.
Best service. Love love my barista who was the best dose of sunshine. His specialty is 3 pumps of toasted almond and 2 hazelnut. Heaven!!!!

Power lunches are perfect in this spot. You entice clients to think you transported them oceanside from the beautiful backdrop of this spot. Have their classic mojitos with either the filet or ribeye and you'll kill them with goodness. Finish it off with the key lime pie and coconut pineapple cake and you are guaranteed a successful result. No missteps here.
With happy hour energy, the decor also whisks you away to a tropical paradise. And this Crazy Cuban drink is like a Latin lover's kiss. Who can resist coconut rum?

If you must eat, consume 3000 calories. In honor of such lofty goals, have the water chestnuts (OMG, bacon, cucumber and radish with honey dip...that's healthy) along with the St. Petersburg potatoes ( salmon, carbs...perfect post workout). The tuna nicoise is a good alternative to their burger au poivre. That's my idea of beefcakes. Oh I highly suggest the summer solstice martini. Cheers to toasty toes and cozy afternoons!
My latest crush is the Bonfire Chicken! OMG. Cole slaw was perfect side and who would ever think to pair sour cream with the chicken as a dipping sauce. You have me. Done done and done.

One of my top 3 faves in Arcadia\/Biltmore area for burgers. Prefer patio. Never short of a crowd so patience my hungry ones. Have the cart of sweet potato fries, dip in all the sauces. Delux Burger is enough for two but I don't share and my body likes protein. All mine. Oh the veggie burger isn't bad, but why bother. If you're coming here, just eat meat. Shakes are so so good if you can't partake on the beer flights. Love late night runs here to feed my hunger bc the crowd is worth it!

I stinkin adore this place. Gelato. Enough said. And they carry Pokett coffee, chocolate  and peanut butter for my mesmerized lips. I love the pirouettes in a waffle cone. Yes I'm that kid with 3 scoops. And it's next to a coffee shop and my fave brunch spot if you need more reason to eat. I will never leave here :\/

Happy hour in the lounge is til 7p. Amaze balls choices. Loved the caramel appletini. But definitely have Uppercut Cab. Bummed closing at end of month but happy to know you can find them at old Kincads spot. Get the escargot, ahi tuna and also Blue Point oysters. That's just starters!!!!

One of my top choices for steak and martinis. Have the Stoli Doli martini, or several in my case, with the Delmonico steak. If you are watching your waistline, have the 10oz filet. Pair that with the wild mushrooms and potato au gratin. Oh start off with the calamari. Love the spice level.  Nothing compares. This is coming from a Thai person who loves spice and a meat lover.

Awesome happy hour. Love the sangria, grab a pitcher! Of course the hummus is so good. I tried all and plain ole traditional still as yummy as others. Ask for extra cucumbers. My go to is the chicken shawarma with extra pickles. Ooze of goodness. My fave post workout option is the broiled chicken pasta salad or the ahi salad. Delishness!

Happy hour is lively and fun. Everybody is wearing a smile, maybe from all the drink specials or because I am flashing them mine. I prefer to graze over the calamari, lobster tacos, crab cakes and a few dozen oysters. Great spot for after work drinks. If you decide to stay, have the Chilean sea bass or the swordfish. No lie. It's really good seafood :)
Wild mushroom asparagus flatbread is yummy. Artisan cheese plate too salty for an uncomplicated plate. How do you run out of Coors Light?

If you ever have to fill up on carbs, have the hummus with the blue cheese, it adds a different taste so balance it out with the sweetness of the bacon wrapped dates. Top of that with the mushroom and arugula flatbread. Trust me, it will entertain your taste buds.

One of my faves in Arcadia. Awesome energy and always jam packed busy. Staff is happy faces of sunshine even at 5a. The parking lot is a zoo bc it houses everything from Pita Jungle to Wildflower to PeiWei. Get here early or play musical cars for a bit!
Top choices are the Mexican street tacos, lobster tacos and the coconut shrimp tacos. OMG. And have the iceberg to wash it all down!

They have the best coffee and pairing it with the banana nut pancakes and a small fruit salad, I don't know how you can't have an amazing morning. The fruit salad is my fuel with this to die for yogurt and granola.

Couldn't agree more with Yelpers. My fave is the breakfast buzz with an extra shot and certainly the oatmeal. Anyone who can make this simple item so heavenly with steamed milk and vanilla macaron oatmeal will always have my happy heart.
Great lunch deal with the hot and sour soup. Friendly service. And quick too :)

Little disappointed even if you charge me $0.65 a person. Everything but 2 items were deep fried. Not the usual suspects at a dim sum to be found like chicken feet, thousand year old egg soup, etc. because that's what the natives eat!!! This soy sauce collection of finger foods is sub par for an Asian buffet. Top highlight frosted mug for beer and the savory duck.

OMG this is THE carnivore's heaven. There's animals everywhere to delight your tastebuds. You can find cuts of meat for reasonable prices! Definitely come when they have BBQ day. The smoked brisket with Mac n cheese is the best I've had hands down. Staff is friendly and knowledgeable with quick service.
If you make it during lunch, grab the Banh Mi Vietnamese sandwich and crispy egg rolls. Plenty of food and filling for even the big appetite :)
The V1, grilled pork and shrimp noodle salad bowl, is uhmazing. The grilled flavor of the meats scream such goodness. The egg roll and veggies are perfect crunch. Why would you eat anywhere else?

A shared foodie tip for the dipping sauce for pho bowls: in a side dish, mix chili paste, sriracha and hoisin sauces with a ratio of 60\/20\/20 for balanced heat and sweetness. Stir all 3 with your chopsticks and enjoy the meat from the pho without diluting the goodness of the broth!

The building is so beautifully done for an agency. I love that there's a Starbucks as well as an art gallery. Currently the hall exhibit is the Art of Calligraphy. It's nice to stop and explore during the hustle of a work day.

One of my fave spots to dock in between meetings. Free wifi and the baristas like serving you a smile. My fave is the ice dark chocolate latte. Love the leather chairs for curling up or be studious on the patio while people watching.
Have the steel cut oatmeal. With a side of bacon of course. Really good coffee. It only cost you $0.50. Unheard of for coffee!!! Great pre workout.

The ceviche is so good. I suggest adding cholula if you want extra spice. Hands down my fave is the tinga tacos and beef tacos. That's fried goodness at it's best. Awesome staff and fun patrons to chat with!
Personally prefer sitting at the bar or sushi table. Definitely the blood orange margarita will kick off your night or if you like to be a bit frisky, try the Hani Pru with the sochu. Amaze balls!!!

Always sit at the bar. Have Jason tend to your culinary needs. He's amaze balls!!!! Don't forego the tuna flight, any and all are pure artistic beauty. Top faves are the Robata grilled scallops, pepper calamari and ask for the tempura corn (it's off the menu but I'm willing to trade insider secrets). MUST have the white chocolate brownie. Serious happiness eruptions!!!

If you didn't make it for their special on international sushi day, you missed out and I scored! The sashimi platter came with oysters, an amazing roll and nigiri selection. Who doesn't want omega 3 intake like that? And now they extended HH all night every night.Butterfish tataki. Seriously should I just live here? Derek takes care of you like you are the only customer he waits on. When you have Mirnes and chef Jason chatting up with you, you really feel like you own the place! Lala love Roka!

I rarely, correction never, come here without indulging in a steak or dessert. However my curiosity of what is avail to others got the best of me. I have to say the Chilean sea bass is incredibly mouthwatering, add a side of Mac and Cheese and scallop potatoes and you might be distracted from the lack of protein usually abundant. Any of the sides are uh-mazing!!! Service is always spot on so it's always a pleasurable experience.

Best bang for buck. So delish. Grab a gyro combo with a side salad to be healthy. Or go gusto with the gyro dinner plate. Be me and do both. Fresh pita. OMG. I love their food. Happy faces always at the drive thru.

This is quite spacious housing your brainiacs and hipster bloggers amidst the pallets of coffee bags. I like they offer the Taproom Experience with daily HH specials and rotating brews. Wish I had this during my ASU late night cram sessions.

Cute hidden spot with wonderful service. Definitely delish tikka masala, garlic naan and the vegetable koorma. Chai was good but I like mine a tad sweeter. Will be back for their buffet and sampling of my usual faves of lamb vindaloo and kheer.

This bar is a classic in a town of pretentiousness. Where else can you go grab shots and cocktails under $20? And we drink like thirsty camels my friends, it's the desert. Leave your ego in the parking lot. Chill out and have good convo with cool ass people.

Love the staff. The smells here just envelope your senses. Hands down the filet sliders are uh-mazing. Love the au jus to spread all over that juicy filet. The bruschetta choices are diverse though my fave is apple and fig and the goat cheese and garlic is a contender. You can be full just off that alone. If you can manage to have more, have the Mac and cheese and definitely the steak salad or the penne vodka. Ooohhh they have Peroni on draft :))
How I managed to forget to mention the jalapeo and bacon mac and cheese and tiramisu is beyond me....it will blow your mind.
The spinach salad with filet mignon is perfect compliment to a side of Rustica Hawaiian pizza. I love the refreshing ice tea!

Seriously best way to end your weekend!!! Sundays are the best with amazing energy, good beats, pretty people, and half off menu. What's not to like? Get the fried rice, chicken lettuce wraps, pork gyoza and ribs. It will soak up all the sake bombers. Get here and stay all night!
The tuna taco is uhmazing!!! I can't get enough of the spice and sweetness bursting in my tongue. Staff is so sweet and accommodating. Get the grapefruit sushi to clean your plate.

Love the happy hour. Kinda loud though and have to lean in to hear people. Perfect excuse to get close I guess. Only time I use butter bc you can't help it with the cornbread. Love the shrimp tostadas and the skillet dumplings. The pork chile is uhmazing. And if you have room eat the grilled ruby trout. Amaze balls.
The seasonal special is worth a few dollar upgrade to get carpets shampooed. Honestly my fave location. Great service, friendly happy workers and quick turnaround. Happy customer

It's good to lose yourself once in awhile. In food, in wine, in cooking, in love. Let yourself get lost. This squid ink risotto with chorizo was phenomenal with the Malbec. Ooeemmggee. Had the most uhmazing time at this 5 course dinner and wine pairing. Thank you Chef Lou and sommelier Christine!

Let's face it. It's the W. It oozes sexy. It's always going to be a good time. A sure thing. Any one can fit in, just channel your seductive side. If you can't find it, the bartenders will help you in a heartbeat. Best blueberry vodka concoction at the downstairs bar. And he serves it with a hallpass for trouble :)

Happy hour here reminds you why the W always stands out. Sunday is my fave funday with them. Why would you go anywhere else when you can have gorgeous bartender Jen or Alex serve you a buffet of sushi goodness? Have oyster shooters, the hanabi, pork tostadas, pork sliders with quail eggs and of course the hand rolls. Otherwise sit at the sushi table and have Landon wow your tastebuds!

Staff is super sweet and friendly.  Highly recommend the gyro spring roll but get peanut sauce! Wish the gyro pita had more veggies so I felt I ate healthy. Side note, take out order was pretty quick if you are on time crunch.
I lalalala love the banh mi. Get the grilled chicken with the tzatziki sauce and chili paste with extra jalapeos. Seriously. I'm in love. My mouth and belly for sure!

Their salads, my fave is the avocado citrus, are crazy size proportions making it worth every penny. However, not so great on your waistline unless you have self control. The rosemary steak and eggs are best hangover cure with the mimosas. And I can't refuse their happy hour when you get the seasonal beer for $1. Go hog wild. No guilt my friends :)
The Epoisses cheese melts on my tongue. The pork belly hands down the BEST. Arroyo Vodka is smooth but Arroyo staff wasn't about service.

This is one of my top all time favorite places. You simply must indulge in at least a 5 course meal with wine pairings. You cannot go wrong because I guarantee you will be nothing short of happiness bursting in your mouth. If avail, always have the wild boar bacon. Need I say more?
See Monica at window 6. She's a unicorn. Love her. Friendly. Customer service oriented and she makes you smile.

I stinkin adore Luci's place!!!! Not only is it great people watching, you can shop for amazing healthy stuff and eat incredible food. Just the name is so whimsical. I love having mimosas with their acai bowl or the lox and bagel plate. I wish I lived closer.
OMG you have to have the Hama Chili, Crackling Calamari, Tuna Poke and Sunshine Roll. You.will.not.regret.it!!! This oozes sexy and those items are pure seduction.

Great ambience. Amazing place to indulge in delish carbs. Have the spicy BBQ chicken pizza and the funguni pizza (add sausage) and use your Yelp checkin for a free dessert. My choice is the deep fried carrot cake balls. Yes. My sentiments exactly. If you are going to gorge go balls out!!! Amaze balls.

Hands down the best froyo flavors. Big fan of the red velvet, peanut butter and plain ole vanilla. I love the mochi, coconut, chocolate chips, and naturally the pearls. OMG. Pure utter happiness bursting in your mouth. 

Staff is super friendly and it is always clean here. This location is always packed. Need more seating, otherwise you end up sitting on the curb, and dim the lights bc it lessens the guilt of cheating on my diet :\/
Hands down, the lamb lentil soup to die for. Rabbit pate great app. But the panacetta dessert is heavenly bliss :)
Beer or smoothie? Geez the option is hard. Love that no where else will you get that as a choice :)
One of my top go to. Happy hour. Meet up. Show up. Hidden gem. Friendly staff. Love the live music. Food is delish. Patio is inviting. Bar is cozy. Just get here.
Tried the sweet crepes and were a bit doughy than I like. Not a fan of the honey drizzle and could have used more chocolate filling. Did enjoy the amount of side bacon and crispness.

Julia Child stated that people who love to eat are the best people. And if you're going to eat here, you MUST have the mussels with spicy sausage. Oh and a side of Huss Brewing's Scottsdale Blonde beer.

This is golf heaven for anyone especially women. Only place I find large selection of actually fashionable golf outing wear but with a pretty penny. But is golf really a cheap sport? They have great staff ready to assist in your needs for drivers, clubs, balls and even lessons. It's like Legoland for adults. Or I am just a big kid :)

The nori sliders are such a creative and filling choice. The crispy seaweed adds crunch to the ahi tuna. Presentation is eye catching. They are so good. Will have to venture back when I complete my meatless month challenge.

My fave neighborhood gem that is always overlooked. Thank goodness so it can be my very own ultimate cave. Staff is just cool. They stopped serving the ahi sliders as an app. But try the slider entree. You won't be disappointed for a sample of the BLT, sweet and spicy and the peppercorn burgers. If your appetite is big enough, just get the adult size Sweet and Spicy burger with their herb fries. Go big or Go home.

The DJ will make you dance more than eat or drink. He's seriously bad ass. Food is meh. Drinks are pricey unless you do the brunch bottomless where someone has to carry you out from having too much fun.

The energy here is calming but not a "let me take a nap" kind. I love the mesmerizing collection of conversations floating about. Baristas were not super chirpy but a smile is always welcomed. The chai latte with soy milk is seriously addictive. I love the hint of cinnamon on top and pairing it with one of their baked breads is so yummy.

Seriously wonderful staff and so patient with a room full of energetic artists. Love the selection for the kids to paint. They have a coffee station if you need caffeine rush. Perfect outing for date or group function.
Located in a crappy strip mall but best hidden gem amongst the bunch. Can't beat getting tofu for under $1 and bananas at $0.19. Stock up peeps! Perfect feeding of my post workout binging :)

Service is impeccable. There is no bad seat in this restaurant. Have the rib eye with the wine sauce and sauted mushrooms. OMG. I had a major orgasmic outburst. Talk to me with cow that's cooked perfectly medium rare with a side of wild mushrooms. Sold. And then top it off with the dessert. The chocolate tarte with the caramelized bananas seriously made love to my tastebuds.
Prickly pear margaritas top off the southwest eggrolls to end my day with smile :)
The half sandwich and salad combo is perfectly portioned for your post workout appetite. The chicken continental and fruit salad are so incredibly delish, healthy and filling.

Love the location and great friendly staff. Delish tapas and perfect portions for sharing. The sangria is incredible especially the white. Would be better served in wine glass. I loved the mussels, shrimp in white wine garlic sauce and the meatballs. The bread was perfect accompaniment to soak up all the flavorful sauces.
The Korean short ribs are so delish! I love love the shrimp kung pow. Definite fave spot. A bit loud but love love vibe :)
The lobster ravioli converted me to a carb lover...it is scrumptious following the buratta cheese and heirloom tomato plate. Yummy!

I like chill spots and this definitely fits the bill. I adore it even more when I can walk out with a tab less than $25 including food and pitcher of beer! Love that the wings are grilled. If you come and they offer the rib plate, get it! So tender and moist. Falls off the bone. Bonus, the side salad is almost an entire entree. I hear 1\/2 burgers on Saturdays are the bomb. Will be back to test the rumor. And who knew they offered track betting if you like playing the odds!
If you have to get anything, you must have the white chocolate bread pudding. It's enough decadence to make a trip just for that. I did. But then I ended up staying longer. And eating more :)

When you have rockstar staff I'm going to always return and happily eat!!! Love the energy of this spot. Started with the burrata appetizer. The mussels were delish and now menu item. The chicken parmesan was good if you like that stuff. I couldn't resist and had both the creme brle and chocolate lava cake. Serious neutron bombs of happiness!

It's intimidating but makes you want to up your game. Why not? Who doesn't want to be fit and healthy! This is a gym for serious fitness people. Clean. Weights are well maintained. Spacious for those lunges and every torture the trainer wants to put you through. Staff is incredibly friendly with a no pressure sales approach. Trainer Hank is a rockstar and I'm a big fan!

Excellent coffee. Great vibe of hipsters and entrepreneurs docking inconspicuously checking out fashionistas. Can get crowded such that you find some people spooning your personal space. The energy here always refreshes my tired mind and kicks my creativity in gear.
I love their attention to detail and customer service. For a fraction of cost, you can have watch clean and battery replaced. Love it and I support family local businesses :)

Happy hour is til 7p on weekdays and from 10-close as well. Have the crab cakes. OMG. I'm a diehard fan of the scallops, Chilean seabass, the cedar plank salmon and naturally ribeye. Oh make sure you finish with the red velvet bread pudding. Serious orgasm. Multiple times. You're welcome.
Best hangover cure is the steak salad and Bloody Mary. Otherwise eat the red velvet pancakes. Or in my case both :)

Definitely try the gypsy soup of the day if it's the chicken and andouille gumbo with fried okra. The crunch with those flavors will sing to your happy mouth and warm belly. Their staple is the white bean chili soup, seriously good flavors of spice and healthy! I'm not a fan of beans but this was yummy.
You seriously set the bar for the perfect spicy Bloody Mary. It's always a good idea to have one.  Breakfast. Brunch. Lunch. Happy hour. Dinner.

Believe it all!!! Such a change for me to come early since I'm a fan of them in my late night wanderings. Not going to lie, happy hour here is pretty enticing with barrel aged drinks and the bacon fat heirloom popcorn, which was a cheat. I even made an exception to have the chopped salad since salads are not my idea of entree. Hence the star of my evening is the pan seared scallops. Be still my heart 

Some say it's pricey. Maybe I'm a snob but I place higher value on what gives me pleasure.

Not a pizza connoisseur but I do know there's a difference between Little Caesars and Dominos. While I generally like things meatier, I'm all about thin crust. I hate doughy and crust filled with garbage. Just give me Italian sausage mushrooms and some olives, throw in Peroni on draft and we are good. Sure I will have a caprese salad to even out the gorging. This location is perfect people watching, currently loud with ongoing construction but I prefer the DC Ranch setting, more intimate.

Great spot to watch the games bc the patio is open and tons of TV screens to delight your eyes. Taco Tuesdays is good for $2 tacos and $3 Dos XX. Get the carne asada, al pastor, shrimp, and duck carnitas for sure. Generous with meat portions. Not on special but I love the street corn too! HH is 3-7 but tacos are the only deal along with beer. DO NOT order the Corona with Bacardi Limon and stick to the Dos!

Have the hamachi kama with a sauce I want to scrape up, the iron chef roll, the golden dragon roll with the sweet mango will balance out the heat of the red and hot roll. Trust me. I eat 3000 calories. You're welcome.
Try the sofritas. Tofu never tasted so good or spicy like this. And a great alternative to meatless Friday or if you want to be vegan which I'm not :)
Enjoying good food, good company, and good talk. Life is good :)

Mix one part scotch, one part cigar and a dash of sexy and this lounge will give you the new rules of living a good life. The live music especially when it's Nate Huss or the DJs, both inside and out, will keep you transported to a different time of effortless cool. Slink across any of the great rooftop patio seating and I swear you can wish upon a star for how bold you can be with every second!
Best coffee with the most artistic presentation. Good music. Creative vibe. Just get here. Then stay. Awhile.

Have the white chocolate cranberry cookie and the chocolate brownie with cheesecake filling. I seriously am in utter bliss. Not too sweet but just rich and delightful tantalizing partner for your cappuccino or latte.
You MUST have the cowgirl cookie, or two in my case. White chocolate with cranberry, delightfully blissful. This is an instant mood changer with the chai!
Honestly Cartel. I am in love with you. Your staff. Your cappuccino. Your cowgirl cookie. You are utter happiness to me. I cannot get enough.

Happily stumbled here after hike. Super friendly staff even working on NYD. Try the Capture 2 special. I love the Capastrami with tomato bisque. The coleslaw and Russian dressing is so yum. Generous meat portions. Soup was not salty. Only needed sour cream. Would be back again.
Wonderful ambience in an amazing setting. The bruschetta was good but prefer my bread crunchier to hold the flavor. I would recommend the charcuterie board. Service is very attentive & knowledgable.

The egg rolls are amazing, the right amount of crunch to maximize the flavors inside. The pho is phenomenal, fragrant and aromatic to the senses before you even add the fresh basil and spices. They are so unobtrusive and generous with the servings. Definite new fave dive!

You can't beat the food here. Incredible service and much healthier and tastier than Taco Bell. My fave are the mini tacos in an array of al pastor, carne asada and the chicken. Why not add a side of spicy guacamole and chips with a couple brewskies? On weekends, it's happy hour all day with $1 tacos and $2 beers. Trust me you can afford this goodness. Thank you and you're  welcome

Love this oddity gem for the Arcadia area that fits in! Have the Slo Poke which is not sweet despite having blueberry. Perfect melody of alcohol. Choose the No Name if you want bourbon. Just missing a cigar! As for apps, yes have the Pig's Ears. OMG. I can slather the sweet chili on my tongue and be in heaven. The bacon popcorn is like no other. More cheesy than oily as you find at other places replicating this. And have the yellowtail. If you survive this, we can be friends.
Happy hour is til 8p on Tuesdays. Forget taco Tuesday. We do tipsy Tuesday

Love this location. Always friendly cashiers and happy shoppers, sprinkled with a dose of eye candy to tempt you to walk every aisles. My fave spot to get chicken sausage and the best Brussels sprouts. Not to mention they carry local bee pollen for any of my sneezy friends :)

Come during spa week which lasts til Sunday and you can get a massage, facial or body scrub for only $50!!!! I recommend Colleen as she used the right amount of pressure to take out my knots. Feel free to use the resort afterwards, it's beautiful amidst this desert landscape. I recommend having drinks on the patio overlooking the beautiful city lights.

Totally agree with my Yelpers. Get the multigrain bread skinny. Perfect crunch. Love the Grilled Chicken and Roast Beef, add mushrooms and the hot peppers. Warning peppers are spicy! The Chicken Salad salad (not typo) is way generous and delish without the potbelly dressing. Even at lunch hour, in and out in less than 20 minutes. I am a BIG fan!!!
The sweet pork tacos are yum. Grab the salsa if you want more of a sweet and spicy flavor. Generous in portion and wonderful staff!

Incredible service. Spacious layout with windows that open so you always have fresh air and sunshine. Love the big screen TVs too. Cannot resist their happy hour!!!! Best white peach sangria. Grab oysters, both east and west coast flavors for only $1. Must double order the grilled artichoke. That sauce is pure decadence. And I highly suggest the wild mushroom and chicken pesto pizza. That is all. Carry on and eat a lot!!!!!

Loved our waiter but if you are going to charge $10 for a martini, staff a bartender who knows how to make one. While the patio is inviting, the loud AC units drown out any chance of conversation. That would be fine if drinks were strong enough to ignore the nuisance. Epic disappointment.
If don't have the s'mores martini, ask for the toasted marshmallow syrup in your coffee. Oh happiness in your caffeine intake!

Sit on patio or at the bar. Not a big tator tot person but everyone raves of them. I prefer duck fat fries, wood oven roasted bone marrow and the udon noodles with pork belly, what else!?! As for drinks, had me at Sonoran White Chocolate and Big Sky Moose Drool. Oh the beer list is over 20 types of the "real deal." Sweet mother of beer!!! Someone pick me up and drag me out of here. This place is perfect for late night cravings.

You would be doing a disservice to yourself if you didn't sit on the patio. BIG I mean huge fan of the pretzel knots. Eat alone or go wild with the sauce. Cannot get enough of it. Definitely am in hog heaven over the mussels. OMG, when you throw coconut with sambal chili and scallions, it is pure utter explosion of goodness! Naturally my fave concoction to flirt with these melodies is the Moscow mule. Not the traditional version but I'm a bourbon girl. Happy belly happy face.

This is a wonderful experience for wine lovers to have their own collection. I am disappointed they stopped the beer option for those who prefer brews. Plenty of choices of wine but I recommend the Delano Cabernet or New Zealand Pinot Noir. Staff is friendly and personable.

Aside that it has a butcher shop, which in itself is OMG but reserved for another time, MUST have the shrimp tamales and the green chile white cheddar mac and cheese. Serious spillage of goodness in your mouth. The prices are deceiving of the quality fare

Sundays are now open at 9a serving their special burritos. I highly recommend the steak burrito and the blind pig which has chorizo. These are super sized for a big appetite! OMG. Mornings get better here!

Best spot after my workout. Seriously grab a burger with grilled jalapeos and a chocolate shake. You'll finish the shake before the burger makes its way to your mouth. And if I kicked ass I usually grab the short rib tacos too. What can I say? It does your body good :)
Love all the baristas here. Vicki is pure sunshine and Ken has the best smile. Tammy prepares the best peppermint white mocha. She always gives you extra sprinkles of chocolate goodness.

Great eye candy for bar service. Mondays are $20 for bottle of wine and pasta. Have to say the fennel sausage was better choice than gnocchi which was way too salty. But great reason to finish the bottle of wine. Happy hour daily til 7p with great food items like bone marrow and beef tongue sandwich. Very chill vibe.

Stumbled in here by usual wanderlust for cute cafs. And I am smitten. Wonderful staff. The pumpkin white chocolate mocha and s'mores coffe cake flirts so lovingly on your lips to ease you with drips and crumbs of happiness. Will definitely be back for their crepes!!!!
Apparently water is now charged! It is frickin Arizona and tap water. Wow Starbucks.

Hilarious quotes on drinks. Love the encyclopedia list of beers. Awesome patio if you can snag spot. Build your own burger for the same cost as what's on menu but with what you want. Love love the french fries. Was not fan of Chicago hot dog. Overkill on relish. And stop changing the channels on games with less than 2 minutes left of play!

Great spot if you want to tune out on convo bc it's noisy. It's always hoppin so skip the line and sit at bar for better people watching and ease on the wait staff rushing to attend to everyone. Love the Bison burger. Milkshakes are ok if you like sucking out of boba size straws. Parmesan truffle fries are good but I like more and bigger in size please.

Love this cute neighborhood spot, cozy and casual after long day. Staff is friendly but then aren't Thais known for the land of smiles? I'm bias...my fave peeps. The decor brings up childhood memories and simply adore the headdresses. Had the pad Thai and was delish. Order the panang curry with bamboo shoots and level 4 for a kick. Will be back for full on review over traditional dishes like papaya salad and sukiyaki.
Small and cozy. Amaze balls food and off the chart service and wonderful staff. My new fave spot for beer, wings, pizza and Chicago hot dogs. Yes I ate all that in one seating.

I stinkin adore this place. Staff is so cool. Different specials to entice you to stay awhile. Eat the jalapeo honey wings with a pitcher while you listen to the fun energy of the staff. Seriously best thin crust pizza ever. Even the cooks are having a blast!
Seriously good Oreo shake. Staff is friendly and sweet. Classic burger was kinda bland and despite the reviews and tips, fries were not a showstopper.

One of my fave spots and happy they are more now in Arcadia. You will not be disappointed by the quiche or the big breakfast, that jam is the star of the plate. However my ultimate fave is the huevos frenchos. Avocado, enough said. I always have room for the pain au chocolate next to the chocolate almond croissant and naturally macarons. The coffee will always leave a smile on your lips paired with those. Utter bliss

Can't gush enough about this place. I was looking for candles to celebrate my father and needed them on short notice. You can order online and pick up order locally. The pricing is unbeatable! So many selections of floating paper lanterns to choose for any occasion. Staff is friendly and this is now my go to place!

Really good pho here and you can customize the bowl size to your appetite from kiddo to sumo wrestler. Downside they close early compared to most restaurant hours. Usually packed and service will be bit slow. Have good company to distract the rumble in your belly.

Sit out patio fireside and savor the medley of short rib potstickers, duck confit flatbread, and white truffle Parmesan fries. Pure Goodness. Then make room for the bread pudding and coffee to close out your caloric intake. Warning coffee is very strong!

Lunch is a zoo with parking but I love the buzzing energy. Definitely attracts dockers taking up tables. Have the potstickers for starters and definitely grab the lobster salad. I love the snap pea crunch with the juicy lobster and tangy grapefruit. It's generous in portion but bit pricey.

When you can convert a total beefeater to devour a bowl of ruffage, you know it's da bomb. Because I'm suffering a current aversion to lobster, I have said before that the Butter Lobster salad was killer. However it's serious contender is the highly recommended Grilled Vegetable Summer salad. That green goddess yogurt should be all over my face. Oooeemgee!!!! Where did all this goodness come from??? Will not be disappointed.

My fave pairing is the sliders with the house salad which is generous,  add the shrimp for topping. Have the Kronenburg Blanc to balance the kick! And don't forego patio seating to catch the beautiful sunsets :)

Definitely have the lamb burger! Would actually ask for medium cooked. OMG the bun is such a buttery soft croissant roll and the muenster cheese and fresh mint bring the burger together. Side salad and fries finish the combo off perfectly!
You MUST have the mussels. This is now one of my fave spots for my weakness. The sauce is incredible. While there is no bread to dip, the side of fries is uhmazing substitute!!!!
Best sit and wash ever. Their vacuum sucks up anything you don't want, even an unwanted passenger

Can't go wrong with a buffet to feast on amazing tacos. The ahi ceviche is must. Bummed pork belly was out. Veggie tacos surprisingly made eating clean so much more enjoyable. Will be back for patio and dessert.
Love this new location. Perfect addition to this area. While I Loved Baby Kay's here, the remodel looks amazing. Food is consistent with other location.

Couldn't agree more with my tippers and reviewers. Have the Raspberry Martini to start your evening. The calamari is perfect teaser and if you must be healthy have the kale Caesar. We couldn't help swooning over the niman pork chop and of course mac'n'cheese.

Seriously love their happy hour menu. Outside of that, get their wild mushroom soup if it's avail. It is ridiculously good and perfect on a rainy day like today. The calamari is always a go to choice along with a bottle of Educated Guess. Service is wonderful and friendly.

So happy they opened this location. Hands down you have to have either the shrimp or crawfish touffe with dirty rice. The garlic bread sops up anything you left on the bowl and the green olive cole slaw is just deliciously perfect side dish.   And I can't get enough of the live entertainment!
Love the outdoor setting. Food is meh. Overpriced for do it yourself type dining. Superfood salad, strawberry chicken and even guacamole were too bland. Great peach tea on the upside!

Love this location. They serve alcohol unlike the Old Town location. Definitely have the balanced bowl for breakfast or the acai bowl and any of the protein bowls for lunch. And if you're still hungry, have the Jacked Up PB&J shake. Who needs to count calories when you are working out?!!!

This location is lovely with all the bicycle art and relics. Patio is smaller than Arcadia but still pooch friendly. 

If you must have a burger, have the AZ burger with the sweet potato fries. The spiciness will linger enough to be covered by the heavenly sweetness of the fries. Otherwise have the brisket but warning, you may be enacting a Carl's Jr sexy burger commercial from the mess and attracting quite the onlookers ;)
Love love love this place. We have an intense relationship. How can you not with HH from 11-6? Seriously that's love. Best carb indulgence. New crush is the Bianca flatbread

Go big and get the Big Kahuna. Double the meat. Double the fixings. Love the spice. Worth every stinkin cheesy drip of goodness. Oh they offer Gatorade for those recovery days after weekend shenanigans.
The best green tea I've had. The miso soup is so flavorful. The complimentary salad has a great sesame ginger dressing. The beef teriyaki and tempura lunch specials are so delish!

Always did like it as Martini Ranch and being Wasted Grain only changed their game for the better. Bartenders are hot and serve us thirsty camels a smile with your cold beverage. Love the chill atmosphere with friendly patrons and certainly my new fave spot to watch Arizona Wildcats basketball.
Note to self, eat tons of the s'mores pop when you want to stay happy. And if you checkin with Yelp, it's yours free!!!!

Lunch is an incredible meal deal. Service is quick and friendly. Get the Thali platters because you'll get two main entrees, lentil soup, salad along with naan and rice pudding for dessert. I love the lamb masala and lamb vindaloo. I discovered the mango lassi today and could drink a pitcher of it. So refreshing and the perfect accompaniment to the spicy dishes.

Sit on the patio especially this time of the year. Just beautiful layout. Have a Stella and the kale salad with salmon. Seriously so good. The ahi sliders were delish but ask easy on the ginger. And Danny is the best bartender to attend your late night cravings!

I adore the sister winebar Whining Pig. Quirky spot with eclectic people. It's a throwback to childhood fun so be ready to chalk on the walls your inner graffiti artist or bring out your competitive nature on Connect Four. Love the old school video games like Mortal Combat. We ate before but agree that it is amaze balls grilled cheese no doubt. Great wine selections. Staff is friendly, space is perfect for cozing up. Just make sure you like the person next to you ;)

Service is really attentive and on point. I would recommend indoor seating but patio was really lovely with the vibrant colors and decor. Try the salmon ravioli and fried chicken. Both unique and delish in their preparation.

Love the new layout. Sit at the bar and have Gabe attend to your whims. Keenan is a complete stand up comedy act in himself. Food is always consistent. Staff on point. This isn't KFC so don't think you're getting out of there with a fast food budget!

You can't go wrong with any of the crepes. Perfect portions to feed a hangover, share or simply a tiny person with big linebacker appetite. Chicken sausage has so much flavor from the avocado hollandaise sauce. Highly recommend the side of potatos, perfect crunch with serious carb goodness. The Nutella and banana crepe will feed your sweet tooth. Love the decor of fresh flowers and cheerful art work. New fave hidden gem.
Today they are giving away pirouette cookies as part of their HH promotion. Perfect with my white mocha!

Love love love the remodel. Would never guess it was a McDonalds. Bonus drive thru. Staff is on par. Love the flow of tables for parking your cute arse for awhile. Fave is the bar stools by barista or community table. I can't resist chatting up. And you can always hit gym next door if feeling guilty

This is more family oriented and relaxing than the Scottsdale one. The Bloody Mary is uhmazing! Love the wings and donut holes with the filling shots of raspberry, cream and chocolate. Perfect family outing spot!

Great space and love the patio. Parking is bit hassle in this plaza though cool they have electric charging stations for EV! Burnt fried rice was literally burnt. No flavor even with sriracha. Try the bison burger instead. Happy hour is nice since it lasts til 7p.

MUST have the bison burger with egg. OMG that slab of meat is ridiculously good. It's playing hide and seek from the egg. Fries are perfectly salted and crunchy. Too bad couldn't have beer to pair with this but you should!
The hours are incorrect. They no longer are open for lunch. They open at 3p just in time for happy hour!
Loved the remodel. Actually thought I was soaking up ocean kisses and salty air. Beautiful patio. Drinks were meh and service was spotty but it's relatively new for Old Town.

Love the space and decor. Patio is perfect for spring and people watching. Three TVs is underwhelming for such a spacious layout. Staff is friendly and personable. Have the bacon and cheese fries. Or try the wings and there's plenty of beer to choose from like the Wobble IPA and Prairie Path Ale. I dig the bar area with all the beers on draft, though having frosted glasses would be a better tasting experience.

Great setup. Amazing live music. Staff is so friendly and accommodating. Order the cheese bites to start followed by the cubano with tomato basil soup and call it a perfect night under a blanket of stars! Checkin with Yelp and get 15% off your tab!!!!

Try them out via Groupon but upgrade to the Brazilian Sugar Wax. Schedule with Crystal, she's a complete doll. Friendly and quick. I'm converted from traditional wax and soon to be regular. OMG. Hi heaven. You're welcome boys.

Couldn't agree more with my Yelpers! Love the remodel from when it was Spotted Donkey. Great patio and beautiful decor. Have the sparkling rose with the Ocean Salt Artichoke. Must try the Crab Cake & Green Salad or the Shrimp Buckwheat Kale Noodle Salad. I had both! I wasn't impressed by the Strawberry Shortcake bc it wasn't traditional and I wasn't expecting a scone.

Order the Caesar salad with steak, no dressing and topped with an egg and you'll never doubt me or the healthy choices you make. The croutons are perfect crunch with this lightness. Hard to believe the small size is that filling.

Definitely order the crab\/lobster Mac and cheese while it's on the menu. How could you possibly go wrong???? And if you order the Rotisserie chicken it's basically Thanksgiving in a plate. The pork chops are so uhmazing that all you'll hear are sounds of a ravenous carnivore out of your dinner companion. Kayla is incredibly sweet at serving up smiles and happiness. I recommend the Chain Breaker IPA  and Prima Pilsner to quench your thirst.

Awesome brunch! Love the strawberry pure mimosa with vanilla bean sugar rim. Waffles come in a caramel butter. Think about that. OMG the cowboy style two potato hash is amaze balls. Then finish off with the tres leches dessert. You my friend just had a major food orgasm in your mouth. You can thank me and John the bartender for this happy ending.

It is always sunshine and smiles in AZ with the sunny Cobb. Healthy and an overly generous portion, I prefer the dressing and blue cheese on the side bc the salad already has great flavor from the sweet fried onions and the moist chicken.

The patio is spacious, perfect for mingling during Arizona fall weather. If you get a table, ask for Tessa, she's everything to ending to long work days. I'm a huge fan of the Orange Popsicle Blonde and Orange Peel, just the refreshing beer for our desert heat. If you like dark beer, get the barrel aged beers, both amazing. No words to describe this goodness. Soak up those beer carbs and have the crispy pork belly. You're body may thank you if you have the pear and kale salad with shrimp.

If you want a chill pool party without the usual gambit of craziness, grab a chair, get a tan, and come listen to DJ Sean Derek spin some seriously good tunes that will make you forget the work week. Hotel staff is some of the coolest peeps with awesome service. My kind of staycation!!!

Who doesn't think life is sweeter with ice cream living in the desert!?!?!! You definitely can't beat $2 for the perfect treat of ice cream and cookies. OMG. Cookies have the right crunch with delish ice cream. Park in the back if you can snag a spot.

Love the remodel of the spot. Staff is uhmazing and you'll find the same faces at the Gilbert location. Who doesn't want to chill here especially when they carry every variety of my fave Perdomo cigars?!?!!! Drinks are unbelievably affordable. No excuse to not send one over gentlemen! Here's a tip -try the tequila made especially for Fox. No regrets. And that's sexy to us woman entering in this sanctuary.

Attended a work seminar and was pleasantly surprised by this little gem. Almost a mirage amidst the Riverview area. Beautiful decor, wonderful staff and definitely gorgeous landscaping. Love the lake outside along with the Starbucks. Heck 24hour Fitness is around corner but the hotel gym looked more inviting.
Breakfast til 130p on weekends during football season. Have the hoppy bitch IPA though they limit you 3 due to the alcohol content.

Love that HH is til 7p even on Saturdays. You can eat all the fresh oysters for half off and it's not often that you can find a 25yo Macallan or a 17yo Balvenie. Definitely get the baked yuzu crab roll, perfect blend of sweet and spicy. I love you Buck & Rider and weekends too!!!

I love the vibe here. Perfect to end a work week and great spot to just chill with friends. There is no doubt that the bourbon almonds will entice you to drink up. But it's the Mac and Cheese and IPA-battered fried chicken that is the spotlighter. Chicken gravy smothered over the red potatoes and the crunch on the chicken is unmatchable even by the Colonel Sanders himself. I also spied the Steak and Taters as one delish contender. I'll be back often and hungry and thirsty!

Such a cool hipster spot with a retro vibe. Attentive and friendly staff and patrons. Park your butt inside or out, you'll never be short of eye candy. On weekends there's a cover charge for the live music but it's only $3. Drink up and soak in the vibe of being very Mad Men.

If you don't trip falling in love with the interior of the hotel leading to this gem, then you'll trip over the goodness on the menu. I love love love the grilled romaine salad with grilled salmon. Deconstructed but art on a platter. My next choice is the breakfast salad. Who turns down Parmesan crusted fried egg???? Quick for business lunches though I'd like to linger longer. Can't wait until my next visit!
Nice happy hour specials on the drinks. Love the chill vibe. The clam chowder was pretty good with a splash of hot sauce. Love the crab cakes.

OMG. How to create happiness and experience heaven on earth... eat the Holy Sunday. This is serious neutron bombs of happiness. It takes like a churro but on steroids of heavenly bliss. And your butt will thank you for it!

The ahi poke is hands down the bomb. Lalalala love the spicy flavor. My ultimate crush is definitely the Brussels sprouts with bacon. The Rosemary chicken with bacon risotto is killer. Omg!!! Orgasmic. And on Mondays if you order two entrees and drinks, dessert is on them !!!
Definitely order the Grayson Cab with your bruschetta board while it's on the menu!!! Major orgasmic eruptions.

It's tricky but you have to enter through the back to get to this cool spot. Perfect spot to just chill with friends. There's no doubt that the bourbon almonds will entice you to drink up. But the Mac and Cheese and IPA-battered fried chicken that is the spotlighter. Chicken gravy smothered over the red potatoes and the crunch on the chicken is unmatchable even by the Colonel Sanders himself. I also spied the Steak and Taters as one delish contender. I'll be back often and hungry and thirsty!

Happy hour is from 2-7p every day with $3 Coronas. Tuesday's street tacos are 99 cents and Wednesdays for $1.50. Normally under $2 it's a steal for your bargain shoppers. Service is friendly and place is always crowded with happy patrons. The jukebox is always spinning out awesome tunes!

Happy hour lasts til 7p and the brussel sprouts are my fave and great drink selection. Sit in the bar and enjoy the live music. Came here during their Monday $10 lobster special. Definitely worth it but today was last of that deal. Love the bar decor, especially the guitar features.
Seriously love the remodel. The lounge invites you to stay longer. Place looks amazing and much more upscale. Great menu and this almost pars with iPic. Staff is super sweet and friendly.

Tucked behind Seasons 52, this cute little spot is cheerful with its colorful industrial look. Not too crowded or loud, perfect for lunch meetings. Service is attentive and quick. Love love love the hot Indian Spice Chai tea with honey and milk. Definitely have the Quinoa and Kale salad with the organic chicken. Generous portion and the pine nuts and grapes let you forget you're eating healthy. Can't wait to come back for their weekend brunch!

Patio and decor just make you smile nonstop. Come on Sundays for half off on wine and great live music from Miguel Melgoza. However, bummed they stop doing it for all bottles on wine menu like the Caymus. Weekdays happy hour menu is really good, my fave is the slider that comes with choice of beer for only $5!!! The sliders and wedge salad are so good!!!

Totally agree with my Yelpers. Not sure the vibe here so it's somewhat an identity crisis. However, great spot to meet and greet for a first date, quick happy hour or drinks before venturing off. Service is wonderful. Love the Brie and check in to get 25% off your glass of wine or beer.

Such a cute concept and much needed. Small but modern with such a happy menu board. While I'll say my ramen is far better, this is pretty good. You order at the tablets and wait for the yumminess. I tried the gomo house specialty. Was good sauce and perfect noodles but needed spice. Add spice with their hot sauce. Great specials on beer and pork buns. Definitely will come back to try other options.

Beautifully remodeled as a very elegant spot to be seen at. Menu is a pretty dime so I recommend for high-powered lunches or a really nice date for that great first impression. Featured specials center around a featured city. Every item looks incredible but we choose the charred octopus salad (no greens at all) and wood grilled burger is ridiculous. 

Nice little fine print, ladies group of 4 or more receive a complimentary bottle of mango moscato. Drinks specials from 9-11p and there's hookah.

If you get the roasted cauliflower and shishito peppers, have the 805 or the pineapple margarita to balance the spice. My ultimate fave is the lobster risotto. They don't spare the lobster or flavor. You can't go wrong with the staff and the lovely remodel.

The lobster risotto is ridiculously not good for your waist but your mouth will love you. If it's available, get the pork chop special and\/or the crispy duck leg. I love everything here including the staff and menu. Oh have a glass of the Taylor Small Batch Whiskey. The remodel is so open and inviting. Sit outside and soak up goodness.
One of the most unique thai meals I have had. Really tasty place!! Delicious soups
Always the best chicken pad Thai and the dragon eggs are amazing!
An awesome day for a team builder!! Amazing Food and a great Team!

Their pita chips are made in three different styles, Chinese Puff Wonton, Sweet Potato and a Sweet & Spicy combo (photo).  The complex flavors, the spices use and yet, the star here is their smokey chipotle mle Salsa. Wow, what an incredible layer of flavors.

Canyon Cafe's drinks are a must. Names like Grand Canyon, (which is a Prickly Pear Catcus nectar type), Blue Moon (made from Blue Curaao), and Mango Rita are all delicious. Really outstanding. But our favorite, is their Raspberry Chambord flavored Coyote mix. It's a must.

Their charred poblano pepper Chili Relleno, reminds me of some of the best we've had in Santa Fe (photo). It's a fajita marinated steak, with adovo mushrooms, beans, light melted cheese, and a level 4\/10 heat index ranchero sauce, served on a bed of rice. The meat is tender and melts in your mouth. The rice itself is outstanding.

The Enchiladas comes with chucks of chicken, Jack cheese and a three pepper cream sauce (photo). It's fresh tomato salsa is nothing like the mle serviced with the chips, it's light and tasty. It also comes with its own southwest rice and greens.
For dessert, we used our free Yelp Coupon and went with the flourless chocolate cake. It was thick, rich and chewy. Nice!

They also have Irish Nachos, Celtic Pot Stickers, Crispy Cod Sliders, Belfast Burger and Pub Fries.  Oh yes, you can find Guinness on tap, and Magners, aka Bulmers as well. The pub is well stocked, so you certainly won't be going home thirsty.

On our recent visit, we ordered the Irish Nachos for $12.79, which were excellent (photo). They were made with pulled pork and drizzled with a Sriracha sauce. Nice! Instead of corn chips, they've serve them with thick cut potato chips. So much for the famine.
The main take away about The Skeptical Chymist, Irish Pubs aside, is that it's a fun place to go. You will never have a bad time here, unless of course, the Seahawks are losing.  LOL. Go Seahawks!
